{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567041","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567041"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18922"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18922","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18922"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.03,0.75,0.08,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11655"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80222"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11655","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11655"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18922"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65502"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"45"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"4625"},{"type":"tags","id":"4886"},{"type":"tags","id":"5514"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11310"},{"type":"tags","id":"11329"},{"type":"tags","id":"11372"},{"type":"tags","id":"11373"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"},{"type":"tags","id":"12912"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27410"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27413"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29703"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29704"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35820"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80222","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80222"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman presents to hospital with an acute stroke. She has right-sided weakness, dysarthria, and dysphagia. The medical team is planning her care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate initial allied health involvement in this patient\u0027s care?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Delaying allied health referrals until the patient demonstrates readiness for active rehabilitation","Waiting until discharge planning before allied health referrals","Immediate referral to speech pathology, physiotherapy, and occupational therapy","Awaiting completion of Aged Care Assessment before allied health involvement","Limiting in hospital allied health involvement to reduce treatment complexity"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is \u003Cstrong\u003Eimmediate referral to speech pathology, physiotherapy, and occupational therapy\u003C/strong\u003E. Early allied health involvement is crucial for optimal outcomes in stroke care. Speech pathologists assess and manage swallowing and communication difficulties, physiotherapists address mobility and strength, and occupational therapists work on daily living activities and independence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelaying allied health referrals until the patient demonstrates readiness for active rehabilitation\u003C/strong\u003E risks preventable complications and misses the critical early intervention window\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWaiting until discharge planning\u003C/strong\u003E delays essential early intervention and rehabilitation, potentially leading to preventable complications and slower recovery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAwaiting completion of Aged Care Assessment\u003C/strong\u003E unnecessarily delays crucial early rehabilitation that should begin during the acute phase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELimiting in hospital allied health involvement\u003C/strong\u003E compromises patient care by failing to utilise essential professional expertise that can prevent complications and optimise recovery\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEarly multidisciplinary assessment and intervention improves functional outcomes, reduces length of stay, and decreases the risk of complications such as aspiration pneumonia and pressure injuries.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early allied health involvement is essential for optimal outcomes in acute stroke care.","Speech pathology, physiotherapy, and occupational therapy each provide distinct expertise in stroke rehabilitation.","Delaying allied health referrals can compromise patient recovery and increase complications."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","How allied health professionals help people. In: Commonwealth of Australia Department of Health and Aged Care [online]. 2021; cited 2025 Jan 18. Available at: https://www.health.gov.au/topics/allied-health/how-it-helps"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65502"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18922"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65502","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65502"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T11:59:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T12:00:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11655"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80222"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","syn